## ğŸ§  Description
This project is part of the Kivro Solutions Internship Tasks and demonstrates the use of Python lists, loops, functions, conditional logic, file handling, and GUI development.
The application allows users to add, view, complete, and delete tasks, and includes both a simple console version and a modern GUI version built using CustomTkinter.

#ğŸ¯ Features & Requirements
Console (Simple) Version

Add new tasks
View current tasks
Delete selected tasks using task number
Runs until the user chooses to exit
Uses a menu-based system with input choices
Stores tasks inside a Python list

GUI (Enhanced) Version

Built using CustomTkinter for a modern dark UI
Add tasks using input field
Scrollable task viewer
Complete/Uncomplete tasks using a checkbox
Delete a selected task by listing number
Clear all tasks button
Persistent storage using tasks.txt (auto save & load)

#ğŸ§ª Technologies Used
Component:	Tool/Library
Programming Language:	Python
GUI Library:	CustomTkinter
Storage Method:	Local text file
Concepts Covered	Lists, loops, functions, conditions, persistence

